They had a large variety waiting for you to choose with beyond large portions. They throw it in the oven to heat it up, and an even $5 and you get to bring it home. The staff were extremely kind, and the whole atmosphere of the place really gave it a true New York style Pizza joint, definitely pleased. I chose to get a Crab/Lobster pizza, never before heard of, and was definitely worth every penny I spent on it. I would 10/10 recommend to anyone wanting a good pizza that's not some mainstream place like Pizza Hut, and with the experience I had I will definitely be going back for more whenever I'm in the area and in the need for some good pizza!

I ordered online during the afternoon for delivery in the evening. I called after work to confirm my order would be delivered on time. So, I ordered several slices of pizza for delivery:  2 plain slices, 1 meatball slice, 1 Sicilian square and 1 artichoke slice. The 2 slices of plain pizza was stale and oozed of tomato paste.  The "meatball" pizza lacked meat (only two tiny pieces of meat) and the Sicilian square had one piece of basil, was soggy and  didn't taste good. The artichoke pizza is in the fridge so can't comment on it.    Upon my dissatisfaction,  I called the pizzeria and was not offered a refund or any type of assistance.  When I called again, the manager expected me to bring the pizza back for an even exchange.  At that point, it was either to lose a parking spot, or take a complete loss.  I did the latter.   Never again will I eat from this establishment again!
